"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-sophiekaufman-2024-08-01-why-katie-ledecky-will-likely-head-to-her-fifth-olympics-in-la\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"BySophie Kaufman,  Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 31, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrence_Kaufman\", \"score\": 0.9902012784053139, \"rank\": 0.009862278782912366, \"text\": \"Kaufman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrence_Kaufman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrence_Kaufman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On one of the best nights of racing in the pool at the 2024 Olympic Games, Katie Ledecky contributed to the show by extending her reign over women's distance freestyle.\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky dominated the field in the women's 1500-meter freestyle, defending her Olympic title from the inaugural edition of the race in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 337, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9989827048978609, \"rank\": 0.001017875680124633, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky won the race by 10.33 seconds, claiming ownership of all top 20 performances in the event.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Already a legend in the sport, this gold medal further cements Ledecky's status as one of the greatest swimmers in history.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's her eighth Olympic gold, tying her for the most by an American woman in any sport.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 627, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8310018909157646e-15, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also her twelfth Olympic medal overall, moving her into a tie with Jenny Thompson, Dara Torres, Natalie Coughlin, and Emma McKeon for most Olympic medals won by a female swimmer.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dara Torres\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\"}, {\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natalie Coughlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\"}, {\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma McKeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky still has more events to come at these Games, including the 800-meter freestyle, where she is aiming for more history with a fourth consecutive win.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it does not sound like she is done making history beyond these Games.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have been consistent over these last few months and last few years in saying that I would love to compete in L.A. and that has not changed,\\\" LedeckytoldESPNafter the 1500-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999777293654826, \"rank\": 0.00017989875579257938, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That could change.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, you never know.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, I really just take it year by year at this point and I really have not thought much beyond this week in terms of what my fall is going to look like, what my next year is going to look like.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But yeah, I do not feel like I am close to being finished in the sport yet.\\\"\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky broke out on the international scene at the 2012 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 15, she was the youngest member of Team USA at those Games but stunned the women's 800-meter freestyle field, winning gold by more than four seconds.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8464901317413103, \"rank\": 0.1813480779404192, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She would be 31 during the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's already one of the veterans on the U.S. Olympic swimming roster at 27 years old and on her fourth Olympic team.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a sport, swimming is becoming younger; teenagers like Canadian sensation Summer McIntosh-who beat Ledecky for silver earlier this week in the 400-meter freestyle-are quickly working their way to the top.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999588132928703, \"rank\": 4.0664590307143406e-05, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Ledecky continues racing, her consistency is one of the most impressive parts of her incredible career.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's that continued excellence and her longevity that, should Ledecky compete in LA, would cement her as the greatest swimmer of all time.\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No swimmer has won an event at five Olympics.\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only four women have won Olympic gold after their 30th birthday.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While swimmers often swim into their thirties, the veterans usually shine in the sprint events and relays.\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's rare to see the older distance swimmers on the top step of the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if she wants to be there in four years, Ledecky has all the tools she needs to be there.\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 12 years since the London Games, Ledecky has redefined women's swimming and distance freestyle.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She shows no signs of slowing down as she continues to chart a historic career trajectory.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In May, LedeckytoldNBC,\\\"The [2028] Olympics being in LA is very appealing.\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not very many athletes get an opportunity to compete in a home Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are currently seeing the effect an athlete dominating their home Games can have with Leon Marchandin Paris.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999709530134, \"rank\": 2.9047024080817772e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky stepping up to the blocks for an Olympic final in the United States, ready to make more history, would undoubtedly be a special moment in a career defined by consistent domination.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999999985497425, \"rank\": 1.404782137870456e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}]}"